    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's what i mean, even \"tiny moments\" are just temporary. it's like trying to empty the ocean with a spoon. the exhaustion is baked into my existence. it's not even that i want to die, really, it's just that the idea of being permanently at rest, where nothing can hurt me or demand anything from me ever again, sounds so much more peaceful than this. it's the only way the noise actually stops.",
